ch.ecma.csta.binding

Class NetworkReachedEvent

  • java.lang.Object
    • ch.ecma.csta.CastorObject
      • ch.ecma.csta.binding.NetworkReachedEvent
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class NetworkReachedEvent
extends ch.ecma.csta.CastorObject
implements java.io.Serializable
    Indicates that a call has been connected to an external network using a Network Interface Device (for example, trunk, CO Line). This event indicates that there may be a reduced level of event reporting and possibly no additional device feedback, except connection/call clearing, provided for this device in the call due to a lack of network signalling.

    The only supported parameters for the NetworkReachedEvent are:

    NetworkReachedEvent Supported Parameters
    monitorCrossRefID Mandatory Associates the event to an established monitor.
    outboundConnection Mandatory Specifies the outbound connection associated with the call that is leaving the switching sub-domain.
    networkInterfaceUsed Mandatory Specifies the Network Interface Device that was selected. The Trunk Group and the Trunk member are stored in the DeviceID content in the format of TrunkGroupNumber#TrunkMember. Note: This parameter is populated for the following:
    1. When a call is placed to an off-server destination and a non-PRI trunk is seized.
    2. When a call is redirected to an off-server destination and a non-PRI trunk is seized.
    This parameter is not populated for outbound calls that use ISDN-PRI facilities or for the destination of a switch-classified call.
    callingDevice Mandatory Specifies the calling device. [AVAYA QUALIFIED] The value will always be set to 'not known'.
    calledDevice Mandatory Specifies the originally called device
    lastRedirectionDevice Mandatory Specifies the previously known redirected from device. [AVAYA QUALIFIED] The value will always be set to 'not known'.
    localConnectionInfo Conditional Specifies the local connection state of the device associated with the Monitor Cross Reference ID.
    cause Mandatory Specifies the reason for the event.
    deviceHistory Optional Specifies the list of devices which were previously associated with the call (e.g. redirecting, transferring, clearing devices).
    privateData Optional Non-standardized information attached to the event.

    EventCause values:

    • REDIRECTED: The call left the switching sub-domain after it was diverted or deflected.
    CSTA Functional Requirements:
    1. When observing a call or a device in a call, and the call diverts from a device in the call, if the switching function does not provide the DivertedEvent for all devices in a call or for call-type monitors (as indicated through the capabilities exchange services option), the computing function will use the networkInterfaceUsed, calledDevice, lastRedirectionDevice, and cause (EventCause parameter type) parameters to properly track the progress of the call as a result of the redirection. See Tracking a Diverted Call for more information.
    2. After a call has cut through the switching sub-domain boundary to another network (Network Reached event generated), all subsequent events reported for the endpoint to which the Network Interface Device (for example, trunk, CO Line) is associated will include a cause parameter with a cause of Network Signal or a more specific cause representing network information.
    3. Not Supported.
    Version:
    $Revision$ $Date$

      • getNetworkCapability

        public NetworkCapability getNetworkCapability()
        Returns the value of field 'networkCapability'. The field 'networkCapability' has the following description: Specifies the type of network reached and the Call Control events supported by the network.

        It includes the following components:

        1. networkType (M) - The complete set of possible values is:
          • ISDN public
          • Non-ISDN public
          • ISDN private
          • Non-ISDN private
          • Other
        2. eventsProvided (O) - This is a bitmap of the Call Control events defined in this Standard.

        NetworkCapability
